div.p:
Wee doe abhorre then, both the NESTORIANS, who deuide the perſon;
and the EVTYCHIANS, who either confoūd the natures, or mingle their
eſſentiall proprieties.

1 HItherto wee haue heard Chriſtes combate with death;
wherein he might ſeeme to be ouercome by death, becauſe it ſo far
preuailed againſt him, as it threw his dead bodie into the graue.
